childElements.propertySetConfig:
{ "controlWidth" : 12, "label" : "TextBlock1", "text" : "

ARIZONA SUPREME COURT

Renewal Instructions – Certified Reporter - Registered Reporting Firm

Registered reporting firms must renew their registration biennially under ACJA § 7-206(N). To renew, complete the following:

  1. Confirm Firm Information Ensure the following are accurate:
    • Firm Name
    • Contact Information
    • Phone & Email
    • Authorized Contact Details
  2. Upload Documentation
    • Current Letter of Good Standing from the Arizona Corporation Commission or Secretary of State
  3. Certify compliance with ACJA §§ 7-201 & 7-206
    • Agree to Arizona Supreme Court jurisdiction
  4. Pay Renewal Fee
    • $100 biennially (due Jan 1–31, even years)
    • Or $50 annually (due Jan 1–31 each year)
    • Late Fee: $100 if paid Feb 1–28
    • Non-payment by Feb 28 may result in disciplinary action

Questions?

Phone: (602) 452-3378

Email: CourtRep@courts.az.gov

Per ACJA § 7-206(K)(3), registered reporting firms must renew their registration every two years. Firms may choose one of the following payment options:

\n
", "show" : null, "dataJSON" : false, "HTMLTemplateId" : "", "textKey" : "", "sanitize" : false }

childElements.name: TextBlock2
childElements.propertySetConfig:
{ "controlWidth" : 12, "label" : "TextBlock1", "text" : "

Option 1: Pay in Full (Biennial Payment)

  • Payment Window: January 1 – January 31 (even-numbered years only)
  • Amount: $100.00 (covers two years).
  • Late Payment:
    • Payments made between February 1 and February 28 will incur a late renewal fee of $100.00.
    • Total due if late: $200.00

Option 2: Split Payment (Annual Payment)

  • Payment Windows:
    • Year 1: January 1–31.
    • Year 2: January 1–31 of the following year.
  • Amount Due: $50.00 per year.
  • Late Payment:
    • Payments made between February 1 and February 28 will incur a late renewal fee of $100.00.
    • Total due if late: $150.00.

Important Notes

  • Payments not received by February 28 may result in disciplinary action.
  • Failure to pay within 30 days of the due date may lead to further disciplinary measures, including suspension of registration.
  • Firms must remain in compliance with ACJA § 7-206(N) to maintain active status.
", "HTMLTemplateId" : "", "dataJSON" : false, "textKey" : "", "sanitize" : false }
